<HEADLINE> South Korean, Chinese Taipei Players Enter Tennis Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Two Asian players from South
Korea and Chinese Taipei entered the Universiade tennis men's and
women's singles semi-finals here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shi-Ting of Chinese Taipei, the top-seeded player at the
Universiade, downed her Italian rival Germana Di Natale in straight
sets with an identical score of 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The other semi-final match of the women's singles was between South
Mi Ra Jeon of South Korea and Maria Callen of France. Callen lost the
first set 2-6 but managed to win the second 7-6 and went on to take
the match 6-0 in the third set.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles semi-finals, top-seeded Yong Il Yoon of South
Korea booked a berth in the final by beating Alexander von Hugo of
Germany 7-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Yong Il Yoon will take on Pavel Kudrnac of Czech Republic in the
finals. Kudrnac advanced after scoring a 6-2, 6-1 victory over Ling
Bing-Chao of Chinese Taiepi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
