<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC Rebuffs Israel's Intransigent Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Six Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) states today rebuffed Israeli intransigent policies
regarding the Middle East peace process and the occupied Arab
territories.
</P>
<P>
GCC Secretary General Jamil Al-Hujailan was underlining this
GCC attitude at a meeting with the U.S. Charge D'Affairs to Saudi
Arabia on the Middle East peace process and regional issues in
Riyadh, Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Hujailan also urged the U.S. to press
Israel to come back to the peace process which came to a deadlock
following Israeli implementation of its policy of constructing a
new Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
The situation in southern Lebanon and the U.S.-GCC relations
were also discussed at the meeting, the report said, but giving no
further details.
</P>
<P>
Israel has lately launched a wave of bomb attacks against
targets in south Lebanon. And following a Islamic militant
suicide bombing on July 30 which killed 16 persons in a Jerusalem
market, Israel implemented a three-week closure of the West Bank
and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Qatar, the United Arab
Emirates, Qatar and Oman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
