<HEADLINE> American Wins First Swimming Gold at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MESSINA, Sicily, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Suzanne L. Black of the
United States took the first swimming gold on offer at the 19th World
University Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 800 meters freestyle final, Black scored a winning
time of 8:45.82 for the gold.
</P>
<P>
Joy E. Stover of the United States finished second with 8:47.73,
followed by Eri Yamanoi of Japan in the third place at 8:48.65.
</P>
<P>
The swimming tournament of the Universiade began here on Tuesday
with six finals will be contested this evening.
</P>
<P>
In the second event of the swimming competitions Tuesday, Martina
Moravcova of Slovakia beat her Japanese opponent Junko Onishi to win
the women's 100 meters butterfly title. Moravcova's winning time
stands at 1:00.45. 
</P>
</TEXT>
