Glavkos Klerides had blocked an agreement by refusing to give
Turks sovereign equality on the divided island.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriot leader then described as a bombshell the
EU's decision to start entry talks in early 1998 with the Greek
Cypriot government.
</P>
<P>
Greece is a member of the 15-nation union whereas Turkey is
not.
</P>
<P>
The Mediterranean island of Cyprus has been divided since 1974
when Turkey invaded the north in response to a coup in Nicosia
engineered by the military junta then ruling Greece. 
