<HEADLINE> Chinese Taipei Wins Women's Tennis Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Taipei won its first
gold medal at the 19th World University Games thanks to the victory of
Wang Shi-Ting and Hsu Hsueh-Li in the women's tennis doubles final.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shi-Ting, the top-seeded player in the women's singles,
combined with teammate Hsu to beat Magdalena Feistel and Katarzyina
Teodorowicz of Poland 4-6, 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Wang and Hsu had a slow start and lost the first set 4-6. They
improved their performances in the second set and after that the match
became easier for them.
</P>
<P>
They totally dominated the second and third sets and won in 6-2,
6-1.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal is shared by shinobu Asagoe and Seiko Okamoto of
Japan and Patricia Markova and martina Ombre Jkova of Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
In the men's doubles final, Yoon Il Yong and Lee Hyung Taik of
South Korea teamed up to win the first set 6-1 over Martin Dvorackk
and Pavel Kudrnac of Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Kudrnac and Dvorackk refused to give up and played much better in
the second set to force the South Koreans into the tie-breaker.
</P>
<P>
But it was the South Korean combination who eventually won the
tie-breaker and the match.
</P>
<P>
Yoon Il Yong, who is the top-seeded player in the men's singles
competitions, had already booked a berth in the singles final after
beating Alexander von Hugo of Germany 7-6, 6-4 in the semi-finals
earlier on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Yoon Il Yong will take on Pavel Kudrnac of Czech Republic in the
men's singles final. 
</P>
