<HEADLINE> Algerian Government Decries Terrorist Acts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Algerian government today
condemned the rampant terrorist acts in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, Spokesman for the Algerian cabinet
Habib Shawki said such acts are "unhuman" as they "target the
civilians to undermine the morale of the people and defame
Algeria."
</P>
<P>
Shawki, who is also the cultural minister, said "invested with
the people's will and the resoluteness of its security men, the
Algerian government is capable of continuing its fight against
terrorism."
</P>
<P>
The situation in Algeria is growing tense due to the escalating
terrorism with the approach of the local elections to be held on
October 23.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 people have been slain in terrorist acts since
the latest parliamentary elections last July.
</P>
<P>
The army canceled a parliamentary vote in January 1992, in
which the Muslim fundamentalists might win. Since then, the
Islamic insurgents have been fighting to overthrow the current
government. 
