<HEADLINE> AIDS No. 1 Killer of Adults in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 26 (Xinhua) -- About 40 percent of all
deaths between the ages of 15 to 59 in the Tanzanian capital are
related to the disease of acquired immune deficiency syndrome
(AIDS), according to a study to be launched here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The study was based on a survey carried in Dar es Salaam
region, Morogoro rural and Hai districts, which shows that AIDS
is the number one killer of adults in the country.
</P>
<P>
In addition to AIDS, the study said, hypertension and diabetes
are found to be common among adults than previous known.
</P>
<P>
The study further established that infectious diseases, most
of which are avoidable, accounted for 50 percent of premature
deaths among adults. 
</P>
</TEXT>
