<HEADLINE> US Inspectors Launch Probe of Railway System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- An intensive investigation of
the Union Pacific Railroad was launched by U.S. federal and state
inspectors following a series of deadly accidents, the Federal
Railroad Administration (FRA) announced today.
</P>
<P>
Sixty inspectors began on Saturday around-the-clock inspections
of the Union Pacific system, the FRA said.
</P>
<P>
Seven people have died in three Union Pacific crashes in the
past three months and five other employees of the railroad were
killed in other accidents since January.
</P>
<P>
The United Pacific Railroad, created by the merger of Southern
Pacific and the Union Pacific railroads last year, operates on
more than 60,500 kilometers of track in the western two-thirds of
the United States with more than 53,000 employees. 
</P>
