<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy, South Korea in the Finals of Universiade Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 26 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and hosts Italy
are in the finals of Universiade soccer tournament after beating their
respective rivals in the semi-finals on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean team forced their Ukrainian opponents into penalty
shoot-out after the match ended without a single goal from either
side.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans showed their expertise in penalty kick and missed
none of their first five tries.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian team were not that lucky as they missed two and bowed
out of the contention.
</P>
<P>
In the other semi-final match between the United States and Italy,
Italy rolled over the American team with the least margin.
</P>
<P>
The match was exciting and full of action. The Italians gained an
upper hand in the first half but could not find the net with their
shots.
</P>
<P>
The deadlock continued until the 64th minute in the second half
when Italian forward was fouled down and the referee awarded a penalty
to the host team.
</P>
<P>
Gianni Califano made no mistakes in converting the kick from the
spot. After taking the 1-0 lead, the Italian eleven concentrated on
defence and gave their American opponents the domination of the match.
</P>
<P>
Yet the Americans could find no way of beating the Italian defence
while at the same time, were nearly caught off-handed by several
Italian quick counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
The score remained unchanged till the final whistle and sent the
host team into the final.
</P>
<P>
The final between South Korea and Italy will be played on August
31, the closing day of the 19th World University Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
