<HEADLINE> Mozambican Police Dismantle Illegal Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican police have
dismantled a large amount of arms in a suburb of Chimoio, capital
of the central province of Manica, according to a report reaching
here today.
</P>
<P>
The weapons, which included 548 mortar shells, 784 rockets, 78
grenades and eight dynamite charges, were destroyed on August 12,
the independent Mediafax said in a report.
</P>
<P>
The police also found a smaller cache consisting of five
rifles and one rocket launcher at another site in Manica, said
Mediafax.
</P>
<P>
Manica was a stronghold of the former rebel Renamo movement
during 17 years of civil war, which ended with a peace accord
signed in Italy in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Another batch of substantial arms was found in the northern
province of Niassa, which included one piece of anti-aircraft
artillery, 222 pieces of shells, 32 land mines and a variety of
ammunition.
</P>
<P>
A Mozambican police spokesman said members of the public
played a major role in uncovering the arms. 
</P>
