<HEADLINE> Camerounian Prisoner Electrocuted While </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Prisoner Ndam Ahmadou with the
age of 32 was electrocuted recently when attempting to escape
from New-Bell Prison in the economic capital Douala, local paper
"Cameroun Tribune" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Frightened by gunshots from a vigilant warder at a height of
four meters, Ahmadou missed the current-free track and was
electrocuted, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The electrocuted prisoner had on him current-proof shoes and
an electricity tester, according to Njeng Daniel, administrator
of the prison yard.
</P>
<P>
The escapist was imprisoned on June 1994 on charges of murder
and illegal possession of fire arms. He was one of the 300
jail-birds incarcerated in the prison for similar crimes.
</P>
<P>
Had Ahmadou escaped, he would have joined Suh Godwill and Fon
Bernard who had successfully vanished from the prison yard during
the past eight months, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
New-Bell Prison yard has some 200 inmates who attempt to
escape every day but watchful warders thwart their efforts.
</P>
</TEXT>
