<HEADLINE> Ratings Assigned to Daewoo Corporation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- IBCA, Europe's international
credit rating agency, has assigned a long-term rating of BBB and
a short-term rating of A to Daewoo Corporation of Republic of
Korea, according to a press release here today.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo Corporation (DWE) is the flagship company of the Daewoo
group (Daewoo) of companies, the fourth largest of the Korean
Chaebol.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo group entities are active in a wide variety of
manufacturing industries including heavy industry, auto
manufacture, consumer electronics, telecoms and IT hardware.
</P>
<P>
Other Daewoo interests include Korea's largest securities house
and investments in the hotel and leisure sectors. In 1996, Daewoo
group companies generated 45 billion US dollars in external sales
and accounted for more than 9.3 percent of the Republic's GDP.
</P>
<P>
The group's current globalization plan has targeted leading
market shares in selected sectors of global manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Like the Japanese Zaibatsu, the Korean Chaebol operate without
a formal holding company structure.
</P>
<P>
Effectively, separate legal entities exist for the production,
export and sales operations, with DWC acting as a central
export/trading function. 
</P>
