<HEADLINE> Shanghai Customs Seizes Smuggling Cargo Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Local customs agents in
Shanghai, China's largest metropolitan area, recently seized a
cargo ship in the process of offloading smuggled cigarettes,
according to an announcement released here today.
</P>
<P>
The local customs investigation bureau reported that ship was
carrying 14 40-foot containers holding 13,000 cases of
cigarettes. Most of the crew fled before the ship was seized by
local customs.
</P>
<P>
Experts point to the fact that smugglers loaded their cargo
abroad and brazenly attempted to evade local customs agents.
</P>
<P>
The announcement made by the local customs investigation bureau
said that the seizing of the smuggling cargo ship indicated that a
cigarettes-smuggling shipping line, which had already operated for
more than a year, was destroyed.  
