<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea's foreign-exchange reserves are expected
to fall below the 30 billion U.S. dollar mark next month, raising
fears that the country may face a serious foreign-exchange crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to a tally released by the Bank of Korea, the
nation's foreign-exchange holdings fell from 33.7 billion
U.S. dollars to 31.5 billion dollars Wednesday. (SKorea-Foreign
Exchange)
