<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rules Governing Behavior of Officials Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Organization Department of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee recently issued a
set of regulations governing the behavior of officials in charge
of organizational and personnel work.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, including six chapters and 27 articles,
stipulate that officials in charge of organizational and personnel
affairs should pay strict attention to theory study and politics
and uphold justice.
</P>
<P>
Such officials should diligently study Marxism-Leninism-Mao
Zedong Thought, and particularly Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, the regulations
said.
</P>
<P>
They should cultivate their firm belief in communism and
socialism and implant the Marxist world outlook on life and
values, it added.
</P>
<P>
They should conscientiously remain in step with the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, and resolutely implement
the Party's basic line, according to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
The regulations call on the officials to exhibit their full
loyalty to the cause of the Party and the people, and to strictly
adhere to the Party's principles and policies governing
organizational and personnel work.
</P>
<P>
They should fairly handle public affairs and strictly abide by
the state laws and rules, and should serve the people with heart
and soul, and seek truth from facts, the regulations said.
</P>
<P>
The regulations also stipulate that such officials should
remain open-minded and steadfastly resist various temptations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
