<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Calls on Nordic Nations Not to Join NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian Deputy Foreign
Minister Alexander Avdeiev has called on Nordic nations to stay
away from NATO, saying that bloc's expansion would have
detrimental effects on the region.
</P>
<P>
Avdeiev made these remarks Tuesday at the Nordic Council's
security policy conference in Helsinki, Finland.
</P>
<P>
He said that the security policy balance in the Nordic region
had to be retained and it was important for Sweden, Finland and
the Baltic states to remain outside military blocs.
</P>
<P>
Unless the Baltic states refrain from becoming NATO members,
Russia would not reconsider its cooperation with NATO and those
countries applying for NATO membership, he added.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Sweden and Finland, too, should remain
militarily non-aligned.
</P>
<P>
But his views were rejected by a number of Baltic and Nordic
politicians.
</P>
<P>
Jan Eliasson, Swedish Under Secretary of State for Foreign
Affairs, said that Sweden should remain outside NATO, but insisted
that "we define our security policy requirements ourselves".
</P>
</TEXT>
