<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Legislators Pass Number of Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The legislators of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) today passed the second
and third readings of three bills proposed by the SAR government
and discussed several motions on resolving a number of urgent
social problems.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session of the Provisional Legislative Council
(PLC) held today, the lawmakers also debated motions on resolving
the flooding problem in the northwest "New Territories" and
formulating a long-term policy for supporting farming and fishing
industries in the whole SAR.
</P>
<P>
The bills passed by the PLC members included "The Electoral
Affairs Commission Bill," "The Inland Revenue (Amendment) (No.3)
Bill 1997" and "The Dutiable Commodities (Amendment) (No.2) Bill
1997."
</P>
<P>
Among the three documents, "The Electoral Affairs Commission
Bill" has been seen as the most important as it was designed to
safeguard a smooth process of the Legislative Council elections to
be held in the first half of next year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before the provisional legislature, some SAR
government officials stressed that the local government has been
and is determined to take effective measures further to improve
the medical, traffic and employment services in the region.
</P>
