<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Rains Rises to 37 in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in heavy
monsoon rains in Pakistan's eastern province of Punjab has risen
to 37, the official Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) said this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Of the dead, 14 people were killed in the provincial capital of
Lahore, the APP said.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rains, which have lasted for two days, also displaced
about 25,000 people in the rain-hit province, according to the
APP.
</P>
<P>
A total of 390 villages were badly affected, said the APP,
adding that standing crops of an area of 25,000 acres also
suffered considerable loss.
</P>
<P>
The APP said that 12 relief camps had been set up to provide
temporary shelter to the affected people.
</P>
<P>
In the past two days, heavy rains swept Pakistan and a Flood
Relief Center has been established in Islamabad to collect
information on rivers' water position and people affected by the
rains across the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
