<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Welcomes Iran's Liberal Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- France today welcomed the
declarations by the Iranian government on the increase of public
liberties and the opening of the country to other cultures.
</P>
<P>
"The declarations of President Mohammad Khatami and his
ministers concerning public liberties and cultural opening are in
favor of a positive evolution of relations between Iran the
international community," said French Foreign Ministry spokesman
Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) nations withdrew their ambassadors from
Tehran in April after a German court linked Iranian leadership to
the assassination of four Iranian Kurdish dissidents in a Berlin
restaurant in 1992.
</P>
<P>
There have been renewed hopes among EU countries for improved
ties with Tehran after Iran's new president, Mohammad Khatami,
took office on August 3.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Iran expressed interest in improving relations with
EU countries, but said that Germany would be the last Tehran wants
to contact with.
</P>
<P>
However, German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel said Tuesday that
he was in favor of resuming contact with the more liberal new
government in Tehran. 
</P>
