launched in October to deliver programming from five television
networks across the country, a senior government official said
today.
</P>
<P>
Joop Ave, minister for tourism, post and telecommunication said
the privately-owned satellite will be sent into the sky by an
Arianne rocket from Kourou, French Guyana.
</P>
<P>
President Soeharto named the satellite as "Cakrawarta", which
means "news weapon", Ave told reporters after meeting the
president.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, which has five transponders with around 40
channels, could be used by TV stations in the country and other
ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) countries, as well
as the CNN (Cabel News Network).
</P>
<P>
The satellite will be operated by consortium Pt. Data Com Asia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia has operated three generations of Palapa
telecommunications satellite since 1970 to support its vast
communication areas as well as countries in the Asia-pacific
region.  
</P>
