<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The '99 International
Horticultural Exposition, to be held in South China from May 1
through October 31 of 1999, will be the largest and longest grand
international event of its kind scheduled through the end of the
century.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhaoxing, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs and vice-chairman
of the organizing committee, made the remarks at a reception
today for more than 300 foreign diplomatic envoys.
</P>
<P>
The showcase event, which will carry the theme "Humans and
Nature -- Marching Towards the 21st Century", will be held in
Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The event will provide a stage for all countries to display
their ages-old colorful and unique gardening and horticultural
arts.
</P>
<P>
The exposition is expected to contribute to the enhancement of
friendship between countries, the promotion of global cooperation
in the field of horticulture, and the advancement of human
civilization, said Li.
</P>
<P>
The Golden Temple, a scenic site in Kunming's northern suburbs,
will serve as the venue for the exposition. Construction of five
indoor exhibition halls and three outdoor exhibition areas is
currently underway smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The site was selected for its variety of ecosystems formed by
the area's unique climate, plateau landscape, tropical rain
forest, ethnic life style and many historical sites. Yunnan
Province is also one of the country's most popular tourist
attractions.  
</P>
