<HEADLINE> Meteorological Satellite FY-2 Operates Normally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Fengyun-2 (FY-2), China's
first geostationary meteorological satellite, has operated
normally since its launch on June 10.
</P>
<P>
Orbital testing has been completed with satisfactory
technological results.
</P>
<P>
The Long March 3 carrier rocket accurately positioned the FY-2
in its correct orbit.
</P>
<P>
During the past two months of orbital testing, the FY-2 has
successfully completed the coordination of geostationary
applications system, including the collection of visible light,
infrared ray and water vapor images, as well as the transmission
of photos of cloud formations, data collection and environmental
monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The FY-2 has fulfilled all predetermined functional and
technological requirements and will go into commercial operations
in the near future. 
</P>
