<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Cambodian King in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China sincerely hopes that all
parties of Cambodia, under the leadership of King Norodom
Sihanouk, will properly settle their differences and make joint
efforts to ensure peace and development in the country.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of China's National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee, made the remarks here today during a meeting
with Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk and Queen Norodom Monineath
Sihanouk, who are scheduled to leave Beijing for home in the near
future.
</P>
<P>
Qiao conveyed the regards and best wishes of Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng to King Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
He cited Sihanouk as being the most respected leader of the
Cambodian people and as an old friend of China who has made an
outstanding and important contribution to the development of
traditional Sino-Cambodian friendship.
</P>
<P>
China cherishes friendship with Sihanouk and attaches great
importance to good-neighborly relations with Cambodia, said Qiao,
adding that China hopes to further strengthen ties with Cambodia
on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk expressed his gratitude for the unselfish and generous
aid China has provided to Cambodia, as well as for the highly
professional and intense care he has received from the Chinese
government and Chinese medical personnel.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk said he will spend the remainder of his life to
contribute to the Cambodian people and to friendship between
Cambodia and China.
</P>
<P>
Qiao welcomed Sihanouk to return to China at any time for
medical treatment and recuperation.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk pointed to recent internal problems in his country and
said that as the founder of the country he has remained neutral
and aloof, while at the same time extending great efforts to bring
about a peaceful solution of various issues.
</P>
<P>
He expressed sincere gratitude for China's understanding of
internal affairs in Cambodia and its support for national
reconciliation in the country.
</P>
<P>
King Sihanouk and Queen Monineath arrived in Beijing at the end
of February for routine medical examinations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
