<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Congress Leader Calls for Population Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The leader of India's Congress
party, the country's second largest party, today called for
launching a war against population explosion in the country.
</P>
<P>
At a special session of the Parliament which began on Tuesday,
Congress leader Sharad Pawar said that although the country had
made tremendous progress in various fields in the past 50 years
since independence in 1947, a large number of people still live
below poverty line mainly due to the country's unchecked
population growth.
</P>
<P>
He said the fast-growing population was the most important
problem facing the country. If immediate measures were not taken,
population of the country would cross the 1 billion mark in
another three-four years by the turn of the century, he warned.
</P>
<P>
India now has a population of 900 million, making it the second
most populous country in the world after China. Birth rate in
India is about 2.9 percent, one of the highest in the world.
</P>
<P>
There was an urgent need to create awareness about the adverse
effect of fast population growth and make concerted efforts to
deal with the issue, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Unbridled increase in the number of people has eaten up the
fruits of development in the country," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
