<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Museum for Famous Chinese Female Writer Open to Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A museum to commemorate the
literary achievements of Bing Xin, one of China's most successful
female writers this century, has been built in her hometown in
east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Bing Xin was born in Changle City and is now 97 years old. She
established herself as one of the most renowned figures in
contemporary literature during a nearly 80-year writing career.
</P>
<P>
At the museum's opening ceremony on Monday, the 78th
anniversary of Bing Xin's literary debut, the local government
said that it has spent 7.8 million yuan (975,000 US dollars) on
the 4,414-sq.m. museum.
</P>
<P>
The deputy secretary of the Fujian Provincial Committee of the
Communist Party of China said that the museum should be built into
an education base for patriotism.
</P>
<P>
Bing Xin, now hospitalized in Beijing, sent a speech to express
her gratitude to the people of her hometown, saying "I hope that
the museum can become a milestone in Chinese literature."
</P>
<P>
The museum has received many letters and telegrams from all
over China, as well as from Japan, Singapore and other countries.
</P>
<P>
Ba Jin, another major figure in contemporary Chinese
literature, did some calligraphy for the museum and Bing Xin's
family members donated many items related to her career.
</P>
</TEXT>
