<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Vice Foreign Minister S.
Muchilwa today praised China for its independent and peaceful
foreign policy which "has contributed significantly to the
promotion and maintenance of global peace and security."
</P>
<P>
"In the past five years, China has been actively involved in
all U.N. activities, made positive efforts in the defense of
world peace, peaceful settlement of international disputes and
promotion of world economic and social development," he noted.
</P>
<P>
China "occupies an important position in international
relations. Its international stature is on the rise as it attains
a central position in the world economy," he said in an interview
with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of China's economic development, saying
China has been the fastest growing economy in the world since
1992 and become one of the leading international investment
centers.
</P>
<P>
China has also recorded "impressive improvement" in health,
education, housing, water, energy, nutrition and other fields,
added Muchilwa, who visited China in January 1996.
</P>
<P>
Muchilwa called for enhanced Sino-Kenyan friendship and
cooperation with expectation of more Chinese companies coming to
the country for business and investment. 
