<HEADLINE> Another 11 Die of Encephalitis in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Another 11 people have died of
encephalitis as of Tuesday in a hospital in Morang district of
eastern Nepal, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The dead were among the 111 patients admitted to the hospital
since mid-July, who came from Morang and its three neighboring
districts.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine patients are still undergoing treatment at the
hospital, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
By August 25, 24 have succumbed to encephalitis and meningitis
in Morang's neighboring district of Jhapa.
</P>
<P>
The mosquito-transmitted diseases are also spreading in other
parts of the country as the monsoon season lingers.  
</P>
