<HEADLINE> Taiwan Securities Executives Keen on Mainland Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan securities communities
expressed their hope to enter the capital market of the mainland
at an international financial conference here.
</P>
<P>
"The mainland capital market is attractive and we hope to come
in," Regina Chen, chairwoman of the Taiwan International
Securities Group, said at the Ninth PACAP Finance Conference.
</P>
<P>
The capital markets of the Mainland, Taiwan and Hong Kong are
both competitive and supplementary, and interaction among the
markets will get stronger, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
About one in ten of the 600 experts attending the four-day
conference are from Taiwan. The meeting is jointly sponsored by
the China Education Association for International Exchange and the
PACAP Research Center of the University of Rhode Island of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The experts from Taiwan agreed that the implementation of
economic reform and opening-up policies has made the mainland a
global focus and a major element for the economic dynamism in Asia.
</P>
<P>
They said that they attach importance to the relationship among
the capital markets of the mainland, Taiwan and Hong Kong after
Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
A successful combination of the financial muscle of Hong Kong,
the production and management expertise of Taiwan and the huge
market potential of the mainland will greatly promote economic
growth in the three places, a securities executive from Taiwan
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
