<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Take Delivery of 4 More Hornet Planes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Four more F/A-18D Hornets
built by McDonnel Douglas are expected to arrive at the Royal
Malaysian Air Force (RMAF) base in Butterworth, Pulau Pinang,
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
All four new generation planes would fly in from the United
States Pacific territory of Guam, the Malaysian national news
agency Bernama reported today, quoting a RMAF spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The planes' departure from Guam was postponed Tuesday when
storm clouds were detected in the Pacific off eastern Philippines,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian air force took delivery of the first batch of
four hornets on May 27 this year.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is the first Southeast Asian nation to take delivery
of the hornets.  
