<HEADLINE> 12 Wounded in Grenade Blast in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 12 persons were wounded when
a hand grenade exploded in a quarrel in a small village in
Catanduanes, the northern Philippines, news reaching here said
today.
</P>
<P>
Julius Ovilla, director of the Provincial Police Office, said
the victims were attending the wake of a deceased relative on
August 22 when a heated argument happened between some bystanders
outside the house.
</P>
<P>
Ovilla said one man in the quarrel was so angry that he drew a
hand grenade and hurled it to the crowd.
</P>
<P>
The suspect is now under the custody of the police while the
case is still under investigation for proper filing of charges in
court.
</P>
<P>
The wounded had been rushed to a medical center by the
policemen.
</P>
