<HEADLINE> Date of 15th CPC National Congress Propsoed For September 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) is to be convened on September
12 in Beijing this year, according to a proposal of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session today, the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee proposed that the Party's 15th National Congress
be convened in Beijing on September 12, as the preparatory work
for the national congress has been basically completed.
</P>
<P>
This proposal is to be submitted to the Seventh Plenum of the
14th CPC Central Committee for approval.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory work for the 15th CPC National Congress has
progressed smoothly. The draft report to be presented to the 15th
Party Congress by the 14th CPC Central Committee was adopted
at today's plenary session of the Party Central Committee's
Political Bureau, and will be submitted to the Seventh Plenum of
the 14th Party Central Committee for deliberation.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, nearly 4,000 people discussed the draft report and
offered suggestions for improvement. Among them are members of the
14th CPC Central Committee, members of the Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection of the CPC, deputies to the 15th CPC
National Congress, Party members in charge of various Party,
government and military departments under the central authorities
and various people's organizations, and leaders of Party
committees of all provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
as well as major military area commands across the country.
</P>
<P>
In early August, the CPC Central Committee solicited opinions
on the draft report from leaders of all non-Communist parties, the
All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce and personages
without party affiliation. Ideas from other relevant sides were
also solicited in the drafting of the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
