<DOCNO> XIE19970827.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Date of 15th CPC National Congress Proposed for September 12 (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 15th Party Congress is an historic meeting to be convened in
an important period when China inherits the past and forges ahead
into the future, and it will be the last held in this century.
</P>
<P>
The congress will hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, review
the history of struggles of the Chinese people in the past century
and look forward to the development prospects for the first 50
years in the next century. It will sum up the practical experience
since the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee,
especially the successes over the past five years since the
convening of the 14th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
The congress will draw a strategic blueprint for the
cross-century development in the country's reforms, opening up,
and the socialist modernization drive. And it will mobilize the
whole party and people of all ethnic groups to emancipate their
minds, seize every opportunity, and forge ahead in order to
advance the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
A new central leadership of the Party will be elected at this
congress. A contingent of outstanding middle-aged and younger
cadre, full of vigor and vitality, known both for their political
integrity and competence will enter the new CPC Central
Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
