<HEADLINE> 4 Soldiers Killed, 26 Injured In Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Four army soldiers were killed
and 26 others injured in a battle with Tamil rebels Tuesday in
Northern Province of Sri Lanka, according to military spokesman
today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said a large group of rebels pounded the troops
with heavy shells of mortars in areas east of Puliyankulam town.
The rebels had also mined the areas to delay the troops' advancing
northward.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with mortar and artillery fire. Armored
vehicles provided close support to the troops and MI 24
Helicopters of the Air force also joined the fighting.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the troops killed five rebels in an ambush north of
the town.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a guerrilla war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the island country
since 1983.  
</P>
