Soft drink company Coca Cola Amatil rose 10 cents to 14.90
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index was 3.8 points lower at 1,381.0, with
resources giant BHP down two at 17.21 Australian dollars on
turnover of 4.6 million shares, Rio Tinto up two at 20.25
Australian dollars and WMC easing six cents to 7.12 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index was 8.6 points weaker at 1,347.1, with spot gold
bullion trading up 1.05 U.S. dollars at 325.25 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 290.69 million shares valued at
863.31 million Australian dollars (638.84 million U.S. dollars)
with falling issues outnumbering those rising by 547 to 454.
</P>
