<HEADLINE> Germany Ready to Gradually Resume Contact With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 27 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel said today his government would like to gradually resume
contacts with Iran.
</P>
<P>
He told a German newspaper that Germany would consider the
willingness to hold dialogues with Germany and the European Union
(EU) proposed by Iran.
</P>
<P>
On August 25, newly elected Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Charrasi said he would like to hold talks with Kinkel, adding that
if Kinkel is interested in such a meeting, it is welcome.
</P>
<P>
Iran is also preparing to resume dialogues with the EU,
however, he said, it has not got any official proposal from the EU.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel said that the German government would discuss with the
EU about the reaction to Charrasi's remarks and whether Kinkel
himself would hold talks with Charrasi has been undecided.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified Iranian foreign ministry official told
reporters if Iran and Germany begin to normalize their relations,
Iran would send a new ambassador to Germany.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Iran and Germany have worsened with both
sides calling back their ambassadors in the other country since
the Berlin Supreme Court pronounced in April that the Iranian
leaders were behind the murder in Berlin in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
