<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Establish National Drug Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
hanoi, august 27 (xinhua) -- Vietnam has established a
National Drug Committee to strengthern the anti-drug campaign
in the country, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Nguyen Khanh was appointed chairman of
the committee.
</P>
<P>
The committee is responsible for assisting the government in
drafting orientations, policies and plans on drug control,
inspecting the implementation of works by branches, coordinating
with ministries, branches, and mass organizations in the drug
control task and guiding activities in international cooperation
in the field.
</P>
<P>
Drug-related crimes have been increasing in Vietnam over the
past years through complicated and cunning means.
</P>
<P>
The customs office alone has discovered 59 attempts to smuggle
illicit drugs over the past five years, seizing 36.72 kg of
heroin, 181.2 kg of opium and 6,666 kg of marijuana. 
