<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Being Cautioned About Poisonous Mushrooms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese health authorities have
made an urgent announcement asking the public to be cautious about
picking or eating wilding mushrooms.
</P>
<P>
The warning came after poisonous mushrooms took the lives of 73
people in Yunnan province in southwest China between late June and
early July.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, 255 people in the Simao prefecture suffered from
poisoning after eating mushrooms they picked in fields in the
locality, and emergency treatment managed to save the lives of the
other 182.
</P>
<P>
China has some 90 toxic fungi which can look very much like
edible mushrooms to the untrained eye.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Health asked local departments to
provide pictures of poisonous mushrooms in their locale for
distribution among the residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970827.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Maintain Growth Momentum, Says Japanese Economist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Japanese economist Hiroshi
Takeuchi said China has completely changed its face since it
introduced the reform and opening-up policy and applied the
socialist market economy on the basis of the reform.
</P>
<P>
Takeuchi, who is greatly interested in the achievements China
has made in these years, said he is sure that China will continue
to march forward in big strides.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua Monday, Takeuchi said China's
economic achievements are obviously unusual with an annual
economic growth rate of about 10 percent and a considerable trade
surplus in recent years. Its financial deficit is not big and its
economic development smooth.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese economist attributed China's prosperity to its
successful reform and opening-up policy.
</P>
<P>
Takeuchi said it is indeed unprecedented that reforms could be
so successful in such a big country as China with a population of
1.2 billion.
</P>
<P>
The success embodies the strength and wisdom of the Chinese
people, Takeuchi said. Deng Xiaoping is a great statesman, who
could respond quickly to the call of history and make farsighted
decisions that conform to historical trend.
</P>
<P>
Deng conducted the planned reform by making experiments first
and then popularization, thus avoiding turbulence, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the reform and opening-up, China began to adopt
a socialist market economy, he said. China successfully
transferred to the market economy because it has a strong and
unified government which boldly carried out flexible
policies. Without such a government, Takeuchi said, it would be
impossible to pursue practical policies.
</P>
<P>
On the Hong Kong issue, he said that without the wise "one
country, two systems" principle, there would be no successful
return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Hiroshi Takeuchi pointed out that the concept of "one country,
two systems" is of very far-reaching significance. The late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping proposed the principle on China's
profound social basis. China has long been good at carrying out
various characteristic policies in accordance with the country's
actual conditions. That's why the Chinese government has been able
to handle the relations between urban and rural areas, inland and
coastal areas successfully.
</P>
<P>
On the upcoming 15th Congress of the Chinese Communist Party,
Takeuchi said that China has made remarkable achievements in its
reform and opening-up policy and the socialist market economy.
However, there are still great challenges facing the Chinese
people. Problems such as state-owned enterprises, the imbalanced
development of the inland and coastal areas all need to be solved
properly. The above problems are not solely confronted by China
and it is not to say that these exiting problems are tougher in
China than in other countries.
</P>
<P>
Finally he expressed the hope that China will make greater
steps forward in its development after the 15th Congress of the
Chinese Communist Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970827.0202 </DOCNO>
