<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails Premier's Visit to Malaysia, Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily today carried
an editorial hailing Premier Li Peng's visit to Malaysia and
Singapore. The editorial reads as follows:
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng visited Malaysia and Singapore on August 21-26
at the invitation of his Malaysian and Singaporean counterparts,
Mahathir Mohamad and Goh Chok Tong. He was warmly welcomed and
given generous hospitality by the governments and peoples of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li exchanged views in a comprehensive way with leaders
of the two countries on bilateral relations and regional and
global issues of common concern. He also made wide contacts with
personalities of various circles and answered questions of their
concern.
</P>
<P>
The visit has attained the goal of increasing understanding,
expanding consensus, enhancing mutual confidence and promoting
cooperation. We warmly hail Premier Li Peng's visit as a complete
success.
</P>
<P>
Both Malaysia and Singapore are China's friendly neighbors.
There has been a gratifying development in their cooperation in
various fields since the two countries established diplomatic
relations with China, and the development has been achieved with
their joint efforts, and especially with the direct concern and
promotion of their leaders.
</P>
<P>
China and countries of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) share extensive common interests and there are no
fundamental conflicts between us.
</P>
<P>
We all suffered from prolonged foreign aggression. At present,
we are all dedicated to the maintenance of world peace and
regional stability, development of the economy and raising the
living standards.
</P>
<P>
We are all following the principles of mutual respect, equality
and mutual benefit and non-interference in each other's internal
affairs; All of us are pursuing a policy of good-neighborliness
and friendship; We are all actively promoting regional economic
cooperation to seek common prosperity; We are all taking an active
part in regional and global affairs and maintaining good
consultation, coordination and cooperation in these affairs.
</P>
<P>
Under the current circumstances, there exists a solid
foundation for further developing the good-neighborly relations.
</P>
<P>
In his speech delivered in Malaysia entitled "Towards a
Relationship of Friendship and Good-Neighborliness Geared to the
21st Century", and in the speech delivered in Singapore entitled
"Strengthen Mutually Beneficial Cooperation and Promote Common
Prosperity", Premier Li said the ASEAN, as an important regional
organization, is playing an increasingly important role in
maintaining world peace and promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
In the speeches, he put forward proposals that China and the
ASEAN countries should respect each other and treat each other as
equals, strengthen dialogue and intensify consultation, seek
common development based on mutual benefit, support each other and
expand cooperation, and bear in mind the larger picture, seek
common ground while putting aside differences.
</P>
<P>
These proposals are of great significance in the further
development of the overall relations between China and the ASEAN
countries.
</P>
<P>
Today, with the accelerating multipolarization of the world,
China faces favorable opportunities in developing a new
cooperative relationship with the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN). We will make use of our individual
characteristics and advantages and adopt flexible ways of
cooperation to continuously open up new channels and expand the
fields for cooperation. We will, on the basis of our current
cooperation with ASEAN, carry out further cooperation in such
fields as infrastructure, sophisticated technology, resources
development, poverty elimination and environment protection. We
will also strengthen our coordination and cooperation in the field
of finance to heighten financial management, perfect financial
systems, guard against and reduce financial risks and guarantee a
healthy development of the economy.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes ASEAN countries to continue coming to China and
running factories. China will invest in and run factories in ASEAN
countries in the form of technological and trade cooperation. In
addition, China can set up joint ventures with ASEAN countries and
cooperate in a mutually beneficial way in a third country.
</P>
<P>
There is great great significance for China in the
strengthening of good-neighborly relationships with ASEAN
countries and the boosting of cooperation of mutual benefit. It is
an undertaking that concerns the fundamental interests of both
sides and plays a vital role in maintaining peace and development
in the region. China will continue to make constant efforts in
this regard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
