<HEADLINE> China's Two Island Provinces Improve Economic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Economic and trade relations
between Hainan and Taiwan, China's two island provinces, have
improved in the second half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
From July 20 to August 7, eight Taiwan groups of 148 people
from industry, trade, arts, education, and journalism visited
Hainan, meaning one group every two days on the average.
</P>
<P>
Their focus was on agriculture, mainly the planting and sale of
tropical fruits and vegetables, breeding of aquatic products, and
agriculture for tourists.
</P>
<P>
The increasing number of Taiwan residents coming to Hainan
shows that China's stable social and economic situation after the
return of Hong Kong has increased Taiwan businessmen's confidence
in investing in Hainan.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural co-operation between Hainan and Taiwan has seen
rapid progress in recent years. Hainan now has over 200
agricultural enterprises with Taiwan invesrtment of 150 million US
dollars.  
