<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Thailand to Join Hands in Fighting Narcotics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has promised to join
with Thailand in an attempt to wipe out the border narcotic trade.
</P>
<P>
The pledge came during Tuesday's meeting of the 15th regional
Thai-Myanmar Border Committee, which is taking place in northern
Thailand's province of Chiang Rai, according to report reaching
here today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting due to end today was chaired by Lt. Gen.
Thanom Vatcharaput, commander of Thailand's Third Army Region, and
Maj. Gen. Khet Sein, commander of Myanmar's Southeastern Force.
</P>
<P>
Other issues rose for discussion were smuggling, border
demarcation and the repatriation of Myanmar refugees in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Northern Anti-Narcotics
Suppression Agency, there are a number of amphetamine factories
across the border from Chiang Rai, Chiang Mai and Mae Hong Son,
jointly run by Thai and Myanmar gangsters.  
</P>
