<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Use Forged Passports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) travel mostly on forged
passports bearing Muslim names and provided by a multi-millionaire
Muslim businessman, a local Sinhalese newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was discovered when the businessman's establishment at
Maradana in the heat of the capital of Colombo was raided and the
businessman was taken into custody by Colombo police.
</P>
<P>
38 passports, 400 visa approvals and several other documents
were found in the establishment. Most of the visa approvals were
outdated and had been brought here for re-validation, the report
quoted police sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Other items that were found at this establishment included
local and foreign driving licenses and the official seals of
several government departments and a host of equipment used for
forgery.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year war for a separate Tamil
state in the north and east of Sri Lanka.  
</P>
</TEXT>
