<HEADLINE> Real Estate Sector in South China City Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the capital of
China's Guangdong province, put 6.3 billion yuan into the real
estate sector in the first six months of the year, according to a
local source.
</P>
<P>
The figure is an increase of 16 percent over the same period of
last year, and accounts for 43 percent of the province's total
investment in fixed assets from January to June, a rise of 4.82
percentage points over the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
Housing is a popular investment. More than 3 billion yuan of
the total investment in real estate in the first six months went
to apartment building construction, a rise of 14.5 percent over
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, investment in office buildings plunged 27.7 percent
from last year's amount. Observers say that market changes are one
of the reasons for the investment reorientation in real estate.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou sold 738,000 sq m of apartments in the first six
months, a rise of 22 percent from the same period last year, with
626,100 sq m being used for residential housing and 51,000 sq m
for office space.
</P>
<P>
Growth of investment in real estate development in the city is
expected to remain at 10 percent this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
