<HEADLINE> Banking Facilities on Show in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China is embracing the world's
latest financial technologies in its drive to upgrade banking
services, said a bank official at the on-going China International
Exhibition on Financial (Banking) Technology and Equipment which
opened here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Although China is still behind developed nations in banking
computerization, the country is moving quickly to close the gap,
today's "China Daily" quotes Chen Jing, general director of the
Settlement and Technology Department under the People's Bank of
China (PBOC), as saying.
</P>
<P>
China will introduce the latest technology and equipment, such
as automatic banking machines, banking on the Internet and data
warehousing, which represent the future of banking, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition, hosted by the PBOC, has attracted 176
firms from 13 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits include banking computer networks, bank card systems
such as Automatic Teller Machines and Points of Sale systems,
multimedia technology, banking apparatus, settlement and clearing
systems, information services and banking security systems.
</P>
<P>
The official said a nationwide electronic network has taken
shape in recent years. About 70 percent of the country's banking
outlets are using some form of computer system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
