<HEADLINE> China to Study Green, Efficient Power Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China will intensify its study
of more efficient uses of energy, which is important to sustained
economic development, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
Improving the energy production and consumption structure,
diversifying energy and power systems and building
environmentally-friendly energy systems are important strategies
for the country's development, the newspaper quotes Chen Yuxiang,
deputy-director of the Administrative Center for China's Agenda
21, as saying.
</P>
<P>
China's problems in the energy industry include: poor
efficiency of energy utilization, shortages and serious wastes of
energy, obsolete technology and inefficient management.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government regards improving energy use efficiency
and reducing coal-produced pollution as essential to sustained
energy development, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the government has tried to phase out
equipment and products that consume too much energy, swap "clean"
technology for coal-based energy, and develop new and renewable
resources such as solar, wind, geothermal, tidal and biomass
energy, it says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
