<HEADLINE> Government Reshuffles Srpska Ministry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Republic
of Srpska was reshuffled at the 11th session of the National
Assembly held on Tuesday evening in Jahorina.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Ostoj Kremenovich, who was in charge of
internal policies, was dismissed.
</P>
<P>
Also among those removed from their posts were Minister of
Religious Affairs Dragan Davidovich, Minister for Refugees
Ljubissa Vladussich, Finance Minister Rajk Travar and Interior
Minister Dragan Kijac.
</P>
<P>
The meeting elected Dragan Kijac to be the Deputy Prime
Minister, Slavk Paleksich the Interior Minister and Slobodan
Echimovich to be the Minister for Refugees. The session also
appointed Drag Simich as the Finance Minister, Vojislav Topalovich
as the Minister of Religious Affairs and Steva Stevich the
Minister of Foreign Economic Relations. 
</P>
