<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Flag Carrier to Expand Fleet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's flag carrier
Cathay Pacific Airways is expected to largely expand its aircraft
fleet in the three years following the opening of Chek Lap Kok
airport next year.
</P>
<P>
A report in today's South China Morning Post said the airline
is now in discussions with the world's two dominant airline
manufacturers about the possible take-up of aircraft during 1999
and 2000.
</P>
<P>
Cathay has options on 25 aircraft with an overall value in
excess of 32 billion HK dollars (4.1 billion US dollars), which
will be ready for delivery between 1999 and 2003.
</P>
<P>
There is believed to be a strong chance that all of Cathay's
options in 1999 and 2000 -- decisions on which are due by the end
of this year --will be made firm, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from these options, Cathay also has 13 firm orders for
aircraft scheduled for delivery from around the opening of the new
airport.
</P>
<P>
Cathay has been stressing for some time that its growth at the
existing Kai Tak airport has been impeded by the lack of new
slots. The new airport is scheduled to have two runways operating
by the end of next year, and will also be open 24 hours --
allowing far more flights than is possible at Kai Tak.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970827.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New 1,000-Lira Coin to Circulate in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 26 (Xinhua) -- A new 1,000 lira coin will soon
replace the 1,000 lira banknote, according to a decree published
today in the official Gazette.
</P>
<P>
The coin will be similar to the current 500 lira coin with a
metal-colored outside band and a gold-colored center.
</P>
<P>
The coin will also be larger, with a diameter of 27 millimeters
compared to the 25.8 millimeters of the 500 lira coin, and
heavier, weighing 8.8 grams compared to the 500 lira's 6.8 grams.
</P>
<P>
The Italian mint also plans to introduce a new 500,000 lira
banknote, which will start circulating within a couple of
weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
