<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Calls for Complete Election in Republic of Srpska </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The political crisis in the
Republic of Srpska should be solved through a complete election,
President of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia Slobodan Milosevic
said here today.
</P>
<P>
He also opposed foreign forces taking a biased attitude toward
any of the conflicting sides in the republic.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic made the statement at a meeting with Robert Frovik,
envoy of the Organization of Security and Cooperation in Europe to
the Republic of Srpska, the Yugoslavian newspaper Vecernje Novosti
reported.
</P>
<P>
A democratic and complete election is the best solution to the
current crisis facing the Bosnian Serb Republic, Milosevic said,
referring to a simultaneous parliamentary and presidential
election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
