<DOCNO> XIE19970827.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy's Tax Revenues up 6.4 Percent in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Tax revenues in Italy rose by 6.4
percent in the first six months of this year compared with the
same period in 1996, the Finance Ministry reported today.
</P>
<P>
Revenues amounted to some 270 trillion lire (152.5 billion
dollars). The increase in June alone was 30.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total included some 1.9 trillion lire (1.07 billion
dollars) of the one-off Eurotax imposed to make sure Italy
qualifies to take part in the launch of the European single
currency.
</P>
<P>
Finance ministry figures showed that most taxes produced
increased revenues, but there was a fall of nearly 54 percent in
takings from the scratch card lottery game.
</P>
<P>
This followed a controversy arising from the refusal of the
authorities to pay a number of holders of winning tickets in
Bergamo because of alleged printing errors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
