<HEADLINE> Egypt to Host Soccer Under-17 World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Egypt is to host the soccer
under-17 World Cup slated from September 4 to 17, announced by a
top official of the government here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for Egypt to stage an international
tournament of the kind. Yet, the organizers are confident of
their capability and sports facilities for the event.
</P>
<P>
A budget of 10.7 million Egypian pounds (about 3.45 million
U.S. dollars) has been granted by the Egyptian government for
reconstructing stadiums as well as other sports facilities for the
tournament. 
</P>
