<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UEFA Honors England, Finland, Norway for Fair Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- England, Finland and Norway were
each awarded an extra place in the 1998-99 UEFA Cup competition on
Tuesday for their fair play last season.
</P>
<P>
England topped the UEFA's Fair Play rankings for the 1996-97
season with 8.57 points, followed by Finland with 8.42 and Norway
8.37.
</P>
<P>
The rankings were based on 900 matches played by UEFA members
up to July 31, including the under-16, under-18 and women's
European championships, the Intertoto Cup and games from the first
qualifying phase of this season's UEFA Cup and Champions League.
</P>
<P>
It is the second consecutive year that England and Norway have
been rewarded for their fair play, with Aston Villa and Brann
Bergen earning their spots in this year's competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
