<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Gears Up for Youngsters' Soccer Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 27 (Xinhua) -- This year's Adidas Predator
Cup will see a big boost as a record number of over 2,500 players
are expected to take part in the two-day local tournament
scheduled for October 4-5 this year at the Hong Kong Sports
Institute (HSI).
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the HSI, the Hong Kong Football
Association and Adidas Hong Kong Limited, Predator Cup will have
extra flavors this year as the best local players are to play
against one another in the newly established Super Group.
</P>
<P>
A total of 396 teams will contest seven age group titles and
the women's championship will be played by 24 teams.
</P>
<P>
Winner of the Boy's 12-or-under group will be sponsored by
Adidas to Paris and compete for Hong Kong in the under-14 World
Championship with teams from over 40 countries and regions
participating.
</P>
<P>
The innovative format of football, originated in Germany two
years ago, has been well received in Asia and was proved
attractive to the local youths when the inaugural championship was
organized here last year.
</P>
<P>
To be played in a turf pitch a quarter the six of a standard
one with no keeper guarding the goals, the four-men-a-side
Predator Cup is exciting to watch and is an effective means in
training strikers.
</P>
<P>
The 378 matches in last year's tournament produced 1,847 goals,
which meant an average of 4.89 goals per match.
</P>
<P>
The local football association wishes that the new tournament
helps promote the game as it is open to kids as young as eight
years old.
</P>
<P>
Six members of the winning team of the tournament will
represent the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) in
the Predator Cup World Championship June 6-10 next year as a
prelude to the World Cup '98, organizers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
