<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Lower Against German Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar fell against
the mark Tuesday as Germany's central bank left interest rates
untouched.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was quoted in late New York trading at 1.7953 marks,
down from 1.8205 late Monday. It was the lowest level since July
21 and left the dollar down 5 percent from a nearly 8-year high of
1.8832 on August 5.
</P>
<P>
The dollar settled at 118.18 yen in New York, down from 118.79.
The British pound was quoted at 1.6147 U.S. dollars, up from
1.6093 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Against the yen, the dollar was slightly lower despite traders'
belief that Japan's sluggish economy means its interest rates will
remain low.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late Monday:
1.4840 Swiss francs, down from 1.4989; 6.0505 French francs, down
from 6.1310; 1,753.70 Italian lire, down from 1,774.30; and 1.3983
Canadian dollars, up from 1.3914.  
</P>
</TEXT>
