<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Slide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Major stock measures on Wall
Street were mostly lower today as investors continued to shift
money from the blue-chip sector into smaller-company shares.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 77.35 points to 7,782.22.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by an 8-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume being light again,
totaling 449.05 million shares, up from Monday's sluggish tally of
388.97 million.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 7.14 to 913.02, the
NYSE composite index fell 2.67 to 475.36, and the Nasdaq composite
index fell 10.29 to 1,591.28.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.22 to
418.31, and the American Stock Exchange composite index, which is
dominated by smaller companies, rose 0.45 to 647.30.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip sector struggled despite an afternoon turnaround
in the bond market, where interest rates went up and down.
</P>
<P>
A number of new economic reports from private research groups
and the government indicated the economy is gaining strength,
which might ignite fears for inflationary pressure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
