<HEADLINE> Russia and Belarus Share Men's and Women's Walk Golds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Belarus have
shared the men's 20-kilometer and women's 10-km outdoor walk gold
medals on the opening day of the athletics competition at
the 19th World University Games here on Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Olympic silver medal winner Ilia Markov beat a dozen
rivals from nine countries to win the gold medal. The Russian
completed the distance with a time of one hour 25 minutes and 36
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Alejandro Lopez of Mexico finished second in 1:26.00 and Italy's
Arturo Di Mezza took the bronze medal in 1:26.12.
</P>
<P>
The Women's 10-km walk gold medal went to Belarus' Larissa
Ramazanova who was timed in 44 minutes 01 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italian Rossella Giordano, fifth place finisher of the Athen world
championships this year, took the silver medal in 44 minutes 31
seconds and her compatriot Annarita Sidoti, Athen world championships
gold medallist, got the bronze in 44 minutes 38 seconds.
</P>
<P>
In the men's hammer event, Hungary's Olympic champion Balasz Kiss
picked up the gold medal with a throw of 79.42 meters.
</P>
<P>
Vadim Kolesnik of Ukraine took the silver medal with 77.16 meters
and Russian Ilya Konovalov came third with 76.16 meters.
</P>
<P>
The women's 5,000-meter gold medal was taken by American Nnenna
Lynch who recorded 15 minutes 47.61 seconds, followed by two Canadians
Lori Durward in 15:48.68 and Sarah Howell in 15:49.96. The current
world championships 5,000m gold winner Romanian Gabriela Szabo didn't
compete in the event, she will compete in 1,500m race.
</P>
<P>
The Universiade athletics competition is drawing 11 men and women
gold medallists of the 1997 world championships and Atlanta Olympic
Games, including men's high jump and long jump winners Cuba's Ivan
Pedroso and Yoelbi Quesada, and women's 800m winner Portugal's Carla
Sacramento. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
